Kenya Kwanza presidential candidate William Ruto will on Thursday take his campaigns to Lamu, Malindi and Tana River counties. Ruto on Wednesday had camped in Makueni, Taita-Taveta and Kwale counties. His running mate Rigathi Gachagua will take the Kenya Kwanza gospel to Nyandarùa County. His itinerary will start at Gathara before heading to Kwa Wambekenya in Kinangop Constituency. In the afternoon, he will be in Kipipiri Constituency and then proceed to Ngorika in Olkalou Constituency. The trail will then visit Boiman in Oljororok Constituency and finish at Shamata in Ndaragwa Constituency. Azimio presidential candidate Raila Odinga will on the other hand take his campaigns to West Pokot-Baringo and Elgeyo Marakwet counties. He will be accompanied by other leaders allied to the coalition to drum up support for his bid. Raila on Wednesday had taken his campaigns to Turkana county.